FBIS4-56791 "drlat090_a_94010" FBIS-LAT-94-090 Daily Report 6 May 1994 CARIBBEAN Cuba ANAP President Announces Imminent Water Usage Fees ANAP President Announces Imminent Water Usage Fees FL0705001594 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 2300 6 May 94 FL0705001594 Havana Radio Rebelde Network Spanish BFN [Text] A fee will be charged for the use of underground and surface water, through motors and other agricultural implements, by the cooperative and farming sector, as part of the measures to correct the national financial imbalance. Orlando Lugo Fonte, president of the National Association of Small Farmers [ANAP], in a meeting with Villa Clara municipal ANAP representatives, clarified doubts and read part of the resolution issued by the Cuban Water Resources Institute. Lugo Fonte pointed out that the fee for the right to use the water will be determined case by case, and will be announced shortly in the monthly Farmer's Pride and Honor assemblies, which are redoubling their efforts against illegal sales of agricultural products.
